.Dd December 13, 2007
.Dt PKG_SEARCH 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm pkg_search
.Nd print information about a package
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl k | v
.Ar package
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
queries the
.Xr pkgsrc 7
index for a given
.Ar package .
.Pp
The options are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Fl k
Also query the Info and WWW field.
.It Fl v
Print verbose information (Ports directory, URL, depencies)
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
The following is an example of a typical usage
of the
.Nm
command:
.Pp
.Dl "pkg_search -v fvwm2"
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr pkg_add 1 ,
.Xr pkg_create 1 ,
.Xr pkg_delete 1 ,
.Xr pkg_info 1 ,
